---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="House Painters Glenorchy | Exterior & Interior Repaints"
  description="House painters in Glenorchy — post-war and brick-veneer homes, weatherboard exteriors due for recoats, rental and interior repaints. Cold-climate prep, low-VOC paints. Free quote."
  canonical="https://hobarthousepainters.com.au/glenorchy/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Glenorchy &middot; Montrose &middot; Rosetta &middot; Claremont</span>
      <h1>House painters in <span class="accent">Glenorchy</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Glenorchy and the northern suburbs are full of post-war and brick-veneer
        family homes, plus plenty of weatherboard exteriors now well overdue for
        a recoat. It&rsquo;s honest, value-conscious territory &mdash; we give
        fixed quotes, do the preparation properly, and deliver a finish that
        stands up to the damp northern-suburbs climate.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Glenorchy</span>
      <h2>Painting Glenorchy homes.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Post-war and brick-veneer stock.</h3>
        <p>
          A lot of Glenorchy, Montrose and Rosetta is post-war and 1960s&ndash;80s
          brick-veneer housing &mdash; rendered or painted-brick walls, painted
          eaves, fascia and gutters, and timber window frames that need keeping
          on top of. These homes paint up beautifully when they&rsquo;re prepared
          right: washed, mould-treated, sanded, filled and primed before the
          topcoat. A fresh, well-chosen colour scheme on a tired brick-veneer
          exterior transforms the whole street frontage. See
          <a href="/services/exterior-painting/">exterior house painting</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Weatherboard exteriors due for a recoat.</h3>
        <p>
          Plenty of Glenorchy&rsquo;s older homes are weatherboard, and in this
          climate weatherboard wants recoating every <strong>7&ndash;10 years</strong>.
          We see a lot of exteriors here where the last coat has chalked, cracked
          or started flaking on the southern and shaded walls. Weatherboard is
          mostly preparation &mdash; scraping, filling, re-puttying, treating rot
          and priming bare timber &mdash; and we don&rsquo;t skip it, because that
          is what makes the recoat last.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Rentals and pre-sale repaints.</h3>
        <p>
          Glenorchy has a high proportion of rental and investment property.
          A clean, durable interior and exterior repaint lifts rentability and
          sale price and is cheap insurance against weather damage to exposed
          timber. We work to a fixed quote and a tight schedule, use hard-wearing
          low-VOC interior paints for fast turnaround between tenants, and keep
          disruption down. See <a href="/services/interior-painting/">interior
          house painting</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Older homes may carry lead paint.</h3>
        <p>
          Pre-1970 Glenorchy homes can have lead-based paint under later coats.
          Where that&rsquo;s the case we prepare lead-safe to AS 4361.2 &mdash;
          no dust-spreading dry sanding, proper containment and clean-up &mdash;
          covered on our <a href="/services/heritage-painting/">heritage &amp;
          weatherboard painting</a> page.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Glenorchy jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Exterior repaint of a 1970s brick-veneer family home, render and trim</li>
          <li>Weatherboard recoat where the last coat has chalked and flaked</li>
          <li>Full interior repaint between tenants, hard-wearing low-VOC paints</li>
          <li>Roof clean and recoat on a tired metal or tile roof</li>
          <li>Pre-sale refresh inside and out to lift sale appeal</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/sandy-bay/">Sandy Bay</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/kingston/">Kingston</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/moonah/">Moonah</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/new-town/">New Town</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hobart-region/">All Greater Hobart</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Glenorchy painting quote.</h2>
        <p>Brick-veneer, weatherboard, rentals and pre-sale. Proper prep, fixed price, tidy finish.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
